    <subsection>
        <title>The Big Picture</title>
        <p>
            We have now seen several ways to solve higher-order linear ODEs. In this section, we will look at some applications and techniques for modelling real-world phenomena that are described by these types of systems.
        </p>
    </subsection>

    <subsection>
        <title>Module Objectives</title>
        <p>
            After completing all work in this module, students will be able to...
            <ol>
                <li><p> Use higher-order linear ODEs to describe real-world phenomena. </p></li>
                <li><p> Understand and perform elementary sensitivity analysis on ODE models. </p></li>
                <li><p> Recall important definitions and results related to power series. </p></li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </subsection>

